fileReport(bytes10,bytes8,bytes2,uint8,i.details: File a DriverReport on a specified Tag

params._behavior: The reported behavior category - from BEHAVIORS enum
params._latitude: The latitude of the geolocation of the report (converted to integer at 1e5 precision)
params._longitude: The longitude of the geolocation of the report (converted to integer at 1e5 precision)
params._plateNo: The plate number of the vehicle's tag - BYTES8
params._state: The state of the vehicle's tag - BYTES2
params._tagID: The TagID of the vehicle's tag. BYTES10 composite of two-letter state code and up to 8 letter plate number

fileReport(bytes10,bytes8,bytes2,uint8,i.return: key The TagID of the key in the mappingnumReports The number of reports against this tag

params._index: the number of the driver report
params._tagID: the TagID of the vehicle's tag

getDriverReportByIndex(bytes10,uint256).return: the members of the DriverReport struct

getDriverScore(bytes10).details: Score is based on severity weighting of all the driver reports.

params._tagID: The tagID of the vehicles tag (i.e., STATE code + PlateNo)

getDriverScore(bytes10).return: uint Driver Score value of driver.

getRecentDriverReports(bytes10).details: Returns the most recent (up to MAX_RETURN (or less)) reports in LIFO order

params.tagID: the TagID of the vehicle's tag

getRecentDriverReports(bytes10).return: numReturned - the number of records returnedarrays of length MAX_RETURN - reportNo, addresses, behaviors, timestamp, latitude, longitude

params._tagID: the TagID of the vehicle's tag.
